<HEAD>Drug-Battling Priests Get Bodyguards</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two Roman Catholic priests leading a campaign
against the sale of drug paraphernalia have been given 24-hour
police protection because of threats from people identifying
themselves as drug dealers.
   Bodyguards were assigned Wednesday to the Rev. George Clements
and the Rev. Michael Pfleger, said police Superintendent LeRoy
