<SECOND>PM-Teen Shot,0155</SECOND>
<HEAD>Youth Wearing Listening Device Found Shot To Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSSIER CITY, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 17-year-old wearing a ``wire'' as part
of a burglary investigation was shot to death by two teen-age
friends after apparently straying out of range of deputies listening
in, authorities said.
   The body of Dramonte Smith was found Wednesday in a wooded area
in lower Bossier Parish, sheriff's deputies said. He had been shot
several times.
   Deputies investigating several thefts and automobile burglaries
said they questioned Smith on Monday and that he agreed to wear the
listening device. However, deputies lost contact with him, and he
was shot Tuesday, authorities said.
   Bryan Widenhouse and Dwayne Moseley, both 17, were charged with
murder, said Deputy Don Rittenberry.
   Deputies said they believe Moseley and Widenhouse, who had also
been questioned about the burglaries, lured Smith to the woods on
the pretext of picking up a stolen rifle.
