<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Europe-Ivory     08-17 0110</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Europe-Ivory,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>European Community Bans Ivory Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The executive arm of the European
Community said Thursday it has adopted a ban on imports of ivory
from African elephants.
   Carlo Ripa di Meana, who is in charge of environmental affairs
for the European Commission, said the decision shows the desire of
the 12-nation trading bloc to protect animals threatened with
extinction.
   The commission decided Aug. 11 to enforce the ban. It earlier had
told member nations they should no longer approve permits for ivory
imports.
   An international conference on trading in endangered species will
be held in October to decide whether to prohibit trafficking in
ivory.
