<HEAD>Duchess of York Writes Children's Books</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sarah, the Duchess of York, has written two
children's books based on her experiences as a pilot, Simon &amp;
Schuster said Thursday.
   ``Budgie the Little Helicopter,'' and ``Budgie at Bendick's
Point,'' aimed at children ages 3 to 6, will be published Sept. 11.
   Budgie was the nickname the duchess gave the Jet Ranger
helicopter she trained on in 1987.
   In the books, Budgie has a pal, Pippa, modeled after the Piper
Warrior the duchess used while working toward her private pilot's
license. Another character is Lionel the Lynx; the duchess's
husband, Prince Andrew, is a pilot in the Royal Navy and frequently
flies Lynx helicopters.
