<DOCNO> AP890817-0120 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-08-17-89 1627EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r w AM-Medfly     08-17 0178</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Medfly,170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Officials Pin Hopes on Dropped Flies at Stadium</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities have restricted fruit and vegetable
shipments from a 70-square-mile area around Dodger Stadium to keep
Mediterranean fruit flies confined to the Los Angeles area, the
Agriculture Department said Thursday.
   Larry B. Slagle, acting administrator of the department's Animal
and Health Inspection Service, said the quarantine and other
measures were ordered following the discovery in the last three
weeks of 40 adult Medflies and 40 larvae in a three-mile-square area
of the county.
   The quarantine ``restricts the movement of all fruits and
vegetables leaving the area,'' he said.
   Medflies are considered among the most destructive pests of
fruits and vegetables. Females lay eggs inside ripe fruit and
vegetables, and the developing larvae feed on the pulp, destroying
their commercial and nutritive values, Slagle said.
   An aerial drop of sexually sterile Medflies is scheduled to begin
Aug. 21.
   ``By releasing large numbers of sterile flies, we eliminate the
possibility of two fertile Medflies mating, so the pest literally
breeds itself out of existence,'' Slagle said.
</TEXT>
