   The Commerce Department reported the June U.S. trade deficit
narrowed to $8.17 billion from a revised $10.08 billion in May.
Exports increased 1.5 percent to a record level of $30.91 billion
while imports fell 3.6 percent to $39.08 billion.
   ``The concern is that the gap shows the economy was stronger than
