<SECOND>AM-GE-Engine Order,0109</SECOND>
<HEAD>Air Inter Orders $200 Million in Jet Engines from GE Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EVENDALE, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Air Inter, France's domestic airline, has
ordered $200 million worth of jet engines from CFM International to
power seven Airbus Industrie jetliners, the engine maker announced
Thursday.
   The order also includes options for engines for eight additional
Airbus A321 jets, company officials said.
   CFM International, based in Cincinnati, is a joint venture of
General Electric Co. and the French engine manufacturer SNECMA. GE's
main jet engine-building plant is located in Evendale, a Cincinnati
suburb.
   Air Inter is expected to receive the jets between 1994 and 1999.
